---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';

const langs = [
  {
    name: 'Rust',
    href: '/docs/workers/rust/',
    status: 'reference SDK · #[handler] proc-macro',
    snippet: `#[handler(topic = "http.call")]
async fn http_call(task: &ExternalTask)
    -> Result<HandlerResult, HandlerError> { /* ... */ }`,
  },
  {
    name: 'Java',
    href: '/docs/workers/java/',
    status: '21+ · @TaskHandler annotation',
    snippet: `@TaskHandler(topic = "http.call")
public class HttpCallHandler implements Handler {
  public HandlerResult handle(ExternalTask t) { /* ... */ }
}`,
  },
  {
    name: 'Python',
    href: '/docs/workers/python/',
    status: '3.11+ · @handler decorator',
    snippet: `@handler(topic="http.call")
async def http_call(task: ExternalTask) -> Complete:
    return Complete([Variable.string("status", "ok")])`,
  },
  {
    name: 'Node (TS)',
    href: '/docs/workers/node/',
    status: 'defineHandler builder',
    snippet: `export const httpCall = defineHandler({
  topic: "http.call",
  async handle(task) { return HandlerResult.complete([]); },
});`,
  },
  {
    name: 'Go',
    href: '/docs/workers/go/',
    status: '1.22+ · Register(topic, fn)',
    snippet: `runner.Register("http.call", func(ctx context.Context, t *cw.ExternalTask)
    (*cw.Result, error) { return cw.Complete(), nil })`,
  },
];
---
<DocsLayout title="Workers">
  <h1>Workers</h1>
  <p>
    Conduit orchestrates; <strong>workers execute</strong>. A <code>serviceTask</code> carries a
    <code>&lt;conduit:taskTopic&gt;</code> that the engine uses purely as a routing label — it knows
    nothing about HTTP, gRPC, Kafka, or any other transport. Workers poll the engine, run the
    side effect, and report the outcome back.
  </p>

  <p>
    Reference SDKs ship in the engine's repo at <a href="https://github.com/kinarix/conduit/tree/main/workers" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><code>workers/</code></a>,
    one independent build per language. Each SDK conforms to a single language-agnostic wire contract
    (<a href="/docs/workers/protocol/">PROTOCOL</a>) and exposes registration sugar native to its host language.
  </p>

  <h2>What is an external task?</h2>
  <p>
    An <strong>external task</strong> is a regular <code>&lt;bpmn:serviceTask&gt;</code> with a
    <code>&lt;conduit:taskTopic&gt;</code> extension element. The element type is ordinary BPMN; the
    topic is what tells the engine "don't run this yourself — hand it off to a worker." There is no
    separate <code>ExternalTask</code> element kind in Conduit.
  </p>
  <pre class="intro-snippet"><code>{`<bpmn:serviceTask id="ping" name="Ping URL">
  <bpmn:extensionElements>
    <conduit:taskTopic>http.call</conduit:taskTopic>
  </bpmn:extensionElements>
</bpmn:serviceTask>`}</code></pre>
  <p>
    The engine writes the task into its job queue, workers poll
    <code>/api/v1/external-tasks/fetch-and-lock</code> for tasks matching their topic, run the side
    effect, and report back via <code>/complete</code>, <code>/failure</code>, or
    <code>/bpmn-error</code>. The "external task" name refers to the runtime mode and the API path,
    not a BPMN element. See the
    <a href="/docs/elements/service-task/">Service Task element page</a> for the full element
    reference, including the alternative HTTP-push mode (deprecated; replaced by the reference HTTP
    worker).
  </p>

  <h2>Pick your language</h2>

  <div class="lang-grid">
    {langs.map(lang => (
      <a href={lang.href} class="lang-card">
        <div class="lang-name">{lang.name}</div>
        <div class="lang-status">{lang.status}</div>
        <pre class="lang-snippet"><code>{lang.snippet}</code></pre>
      </a>
    ))}
  </div>

  <h2>Cross-cutting</h2>

  <div class="doc-cards">
    <a href="/docs/workers/protocol/" class="doc-card">
      <div class="card-icon">📡</div>
      <h3>Protocol</h3>
      <p>The five endpoints under <code>/api/v1/external-tasks/*</code>, the JSON variable shape, the
      <code>U</code>/<code>S</code> error envelope, and the at-least-once semantic contract.</p>
      <span class="card-link">Read the wire contract →</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/docs/workers/idempotency/" class="doc-card">
      <div class="card-icon">♻️</div>
      <h3>Idempotency</h3>
      <p>At-least-once means workers can see the same task twice. Per-handler strategies for HTTP,
      CSV, GCS, and Kafka producers; the optional Postgres dedupe store.</p>
      <span class="card-link">Make it safe →</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/docs/workers/examples/" class="doc-card">
      <div class="card-icon">🧪</div>
      <h3>Examples</h3>
      <p>End-to-end pairs: a tiny BPMN with <code>&lt;conduit:taskTopic&gt;</code> alongside the worker
      that handles it. One example per SDK.</p>
      <span class="card-link">See it run →</span>
    </a>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .lang-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(320px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem;
  }
  .lang-card {
    display: block;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.15s, background 0.15s;
  }
  .lang-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    background: var(--color-surface-2);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .lang-name {
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .lang-status {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .lang-snippet {
    margin: 0;
    background: var(--color-bg);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
    overflow-x: auto;
    white-space: pre;
  }
  .lang-snippet code { color: var(--color-text); font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; }

  .intro-snippet {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    white-space: pre;
  }
  .intro-snippet code { color: var(--color-text); font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; }

  .doc-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  .doc-card {
    display: block;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.15s, background 0.15s;
  }
  .doc-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    background: var(--color-surface-2);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .card-icon { font-size: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .doc-card h3 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; color: #fff; }
  .doc-card p { margin: 0 0 0.85rem; color: var(--color-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .card-link { color: var(--color-accent-light); font-size: 0.9rem; }
</style>
